\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 What did your mother do if you did something she didn't like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Nothing. Nothing, we were more or legs toge
ther, it's surprising that. And of course she would sit on the machine, it wasn't the power machine like I've got, treadl}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6104996\charrsid3306671 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 
, you know, and then - I'd have to mind the baby. And then the other one, this is Ben, she used to say - oh put him on the back of my 
chair. And she used to have him on the back of her chair with a calendar, she used - 'cos she had gorgeous long dark chestnut hair, and she'd }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6104996\charrsid3306671 always}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671  cut bits off you know, tie it on a match-stick and get them to paint. Yes, she was - yes. Keep the children
 happy. She used to say - yes, she used to say, oh, let them do some drawing, and she - this lovely long hair, she'd cut a bit off, tie it on a matchstick with some of her cotton and give the children a little paintbrush. Yes, yes. I wouldn't say we never
 had toys, well I didn't - not so much as that, but the children - they - they would play for hours with - bus tickets. And bend the ends - split them and bend the ends and stand up. When you consider what the children have now you -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 When your mother was working there wasn't a neighbour or relative who came in to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Oh no. No. Only me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 You did it all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Yes. But, she was always willing - you'd be surprised how the - as a family - this kind of a home you know, anyone could come in, and 
she'd always be ready to help anyone. Yes. Anyone ill, she would go - go in - I wouldn't say, as I tell you, we weren't religious but - she - Mrs Panning died next door to us and she went in, she said, oh I didn't like her pillow cases, I thought they loo
ked }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6104996\charrsid3306671 greasy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 
. So she took her in - took her in a couple of her pillowcases, I couldn't let her die with dirty pillowcases, and then she took them in, she said, would you like me to say a prayer for you? And she knelt down, said the Lord's Prayer. I thought - 
oh, I don't know - think I could mum. Yes. Yes. And of course at the - the same time when she was machining she was singing away at the top of her voice - her voice, Tell me the old, old story, you know, and it - up and down - oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Always hymns?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Yes, always hymns. Mostly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 There were some other songs were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 
No. No. It was mostly hymns. I think she got it from her own mother, she - when she used to talk to me a lot - about her - her young life. But she didn't have much of a life poor dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Did you all sing together then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 
Oh yes, we'd do it the same. Shriek at the top of - Tell me the old, old story. Of course I can't do it now. And - oh another one - oh - the old Easter hymns, you know, those very up and down. Oh poor 
mum if only she could have had a power machine. I've thought of her since, how she - and of course she did work right to the last light of having her babies. And I didn't know at that time, only a little girl, I - she used - but I knew she was sitting in 
this chair at the side and looking awful, and I thought, oh another baby. But I didn't understand what was happening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 They never told you when a baby was coming?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 No. No. No. I didn't understand, and then she would make me polish this - you know, 
the old fashioned - kitchen range, with the home sweet home on the fender.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Can you describe the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Which one would you prefer to talk about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Well I should say - the one we was in longest perhaps, about fourteen years I think 
we were in that. No, that would be the Anchor Street one. That was later. The younger one - the - at - Southwark Park Road was a cottage with stairs up the middle and just two rooms each side. Terrific long front garden, and a very back yard, concrete bac
k
 yard only. But a very long front garden, still there now. Well it was. And just - just two rooms up and then we had to use the front room downstairs as a bedroom when the babies came - four babies came. And - I think I went down below. Anyway - I was alw
ays away from school for the three weeks of the - the annual birth, and my teacher, Miss Peagram, she used to come home, visit mum, yes, as awfully - I was thrilled with that. Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6104996\charrsid3306671 
I - I was trilled with Miss Peagram for doing it, and Miss Jones, the headmistress. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 
They always asked me and mum used to send a note to say - we'll be keeping Lou away. And - Miss Pegram then would co and see mum, probably bring her things. I wouldn't know that. But I can still see her going up these stairs up the middle of the - 
bedroom either side. And then the teacher would see mum in one room and then come in to us at the other.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Did all the children sleep in one room then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Well we weren't so many then. There - there was us - don't know whether it was me or the boys 
- in that house. In the one - mum and dad in one side, another lot of bedroom the other side, any tiny rooms, and then when - the boys I think went down-}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6104996\charrsid3306671 stairs}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 . I know we - we used the downstairs front room as a bedroom afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Did you each have your own bed or did you share?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 
Yes, oh we all - yes. Yes. In our - in our Anchor Street house, the - the biggest one, I was older then, and - mum used to say - oh go round the corner and get Mrs Collins will you? And I knew there was a baby coming. So
 I used to go round and bring Mrs Collins. That was all right, she could look after mum. But of course dad, he'd got to go to bed. And I - I - twice I did it, I said, that's all right dad, you go up in my bed - bedroom, you know, and dad slept on my bed. 
Talk about a - oh - of course we've thought about it since. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6104996\charrsid3306671 How selfish}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671  they were. Really selfish. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Do you remember the flat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Well - yes.
