\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 
No, I should say they were different social groups. They were at St James' church - when I was young. Then old - when I was older we used to - probably from }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13985300\charrsid3306671 Southwark}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671  Park Road, we would go
 to this - Clare College as mum called it, where she had all her christenings and I was godmother to the children. Well - there I don't think there was the marked difference as there was in the big parish church. That is my impression.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 So you mean the big parish church would have more wealthy and more poor people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Yes. Yes. Yes, they - because the doctors would go. There. And shopkeepers, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9190934\charrsid3306671 it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9190934\charrsid3306671  in}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 
 the main Jamaica Road. That's right, put it out, do what you want.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Apart from shopkeepers were there any employers that lived in the district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 
I shouldn't think so. I shouldn't think so. I don't remember - because mostly they were factories all along from Tooley Street, right down, you know, the big factories and the wharves along the riversi
de side. So that the people wouldn't be - I think there would only be shopkeepers more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 They would have moved out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Yes, they would have been out. Yes, they would have been. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Before you went to school were you given any lessons by your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 
No. No, except mum did always talk to us. Mind you, I - I must tell you this, but as soon as we left school, right, go to evening classes. One of us - we all had to go. We had to - it was - we finished school, right, you go to evening classes
. And we did - we all did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 What did you learn at evening classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 
Well I did do everything. My main subject, I wanted current affairs. That was my - what I - all the time even with W.E.A. 'cos I kept that up all the time. Yes. Except this last -
 session, I don't - I don't go because I didn't like the subject. Seemed the same as we had last year. And I mean -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 When did you join the W.E.A. then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 W.E.A. - I was in it for twenty years at Hornchurch, I've been here eight years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 So you were in it twenty-eight years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 
Yes. At least, on the W.E.A. apart from that I've - oh I've been up here to pottery and dressmaking, cookery. I - when I was young - when I was single, before I married, I went to - the Polytechnic in Regent Street, I wa
s doing cookery there. Yes. Oh I've always been out - joined everything. I joined everything when I came here. Be - well I was alone. Oh the British Legion, the Conservatives, the W.I. Horticulture. I - that I - I've been in that everywhere. Yes. Yes. Oh 
yes. I -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 There weren't so many clubs going back to when you were younger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 
Not when I was younger, no, there weren't the clubs, but I joined the rambling club, when I was single. I think they - they first formed a rambling club, the Homeland Ramb
lers. I'd love to - find out - it was disbanded, it's a - a national affair now. We used to go all over surrey. And - 'cos that is the point from South London, we would go out from there. Probably by train, to the main point, Sheen and Goldalming and plac
es like that and - well I've always been - been out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 When was that rambling club started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 
Oh it - before I married so it could have been '25 or '24. 1924. Whenever the Homeland Ramblers joined - formed I mean. Formed. Oh yes. No, I - I'm a wanderer. I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9190934\charrsid3306671 believed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 . I think - I always wanted to travel, even when I was a little girl learning - my favourite was geography. Always wanted to go to Canada. To }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9190934\charrsid3306671 
Saskatchewan}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671  and Manitoba, now that was my - I don't know how you say them, you might have a differe
nt definition but - to me it was always Saskatchewan and Manitoba I think it's Manitoba now. No, I've always had a wanderlust. But never been able to afford. I have been abroad. I went with the London University - couple of months after me husband died I 
w
ent to - to Germany. I didn't even tell me - the neighbours knew, because they minded me cat. - but I never told neither of my sons. Peter - Peter came down, he'd just got married you see, was living here and I was - and he came down. He couldn't get in. 
Place was bolted and barred. So he went over the road and - he found out from there that I'd gone to Germany. Oh no, I - I'm a real wanderer. And I would be if I was younger now - now I'm free. Well - I will if Ernie comes up you bet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Could you tell me when you started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Just before I was five. Before I was five. Just before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 What was the school you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9190934\charrsid3306671 Keatons}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671  Road Higher Grade. Mother had ambitions for me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 That was the first school you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Yes, the only school. Well I was only there 'til thirteen. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 I didn't know you could start in a higher grade school, I thought you progressed?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 No. No. Not there. And in fact the others went to the same school as well, but opposite us in Southwark Park Road. T
he little 'uns started from there. And then from when we moved to Anchor Street they would walk down the same as I walked. Twenty - nearly twenty minutes walk it used to take me then, I expect I could do it in ten minutes now. Oh no, we were all at the on
ly school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Was that the London School Board?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Did you go back for your midday meal when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Yes. Always home, there was nothing - no - we had two hours then, really was two hours, from twelve 'til two. Yes. 
And half past four we left. Same with the others - at - that's the schooling in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Was it boys and girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 No, mine was separate schools. And I can't tell you what the - the other }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9190934\charrsid3306671 
children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671  were in Southwark Park Road. But mine was - two 
separate buildings - together. There was a brick wall down the playground. And when we did science we had to go - through into the science in the boys part. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Did they have uniforms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 No. Nothing. Nothing at all. We couldn't have done, not in 
the - conditions we lived. Oh - and I must tell you. The church - the mission - where was the mission where was the mission? It wasn't over the road, the Methodist on the opposite corner. Must have been a mission up Southwark Park Road, the main road, any
w
ay - they had a Harvest Festival. And of course they came down with a blooming great loaf, the vicar did, Mrs Jones. He came and knocked at the door. And asked for mum. Mum went, 'cos we all dashed to the door - or - well one used to always dash, and he a
sked to see }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9190934\charrsid3306671 mum}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 
. Mum - went, and he said, Mrs Gardner, he said, we'd like you to accept this loaf. And mum said, she said, good gracious, oh no, you give it to somebody who's poor. And there's us sitting - it - it just shows - she never thought we were - no
t that we were ever hungry. She was very - - very good manager. And - we did make - it was bread and dripping a lot because I tell you she used to get these pieces, three pound of pieces for sixpence, it would last a few days and there'd be lots of drippi
n
g and we'd have bread and dripping. Yes. But - even Glad said, surprising how we never thought we were hard up. Well mum didn't let us think it, put it like that. We - we knew it because we never had pocket money like some of the other children. But it - 
I realize it now but we never at that time, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Did you enjoy being at school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 I did. 'Cos I liked learning. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Geography was the subject you liked most?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Geography and French. Yes. We used to have a real French lady, Madame Garnier. Used to like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Some of the teachers were quite friends of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 
Very - yes. Mrs Channing was, and my teacher, Miss Pegram, she used to come home every year mum had another baby she would come home and visit her. Probably she brought 
her something, I wouldn't know. I mean, we would open the door and then she would go up the stairs. In Southwark Park Road it was a - a four roomed place, the main room's, there was a back, a scullery. But she would go up the stairs and you'd leave her to
 go up. I - I wouldn't know then, I was younger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Was there one teacher that you especially admired or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Yes, Miss Pegram. I did - she was my teacher. I loved her, because she must be gone by now, I'd love to find out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 What sort of things did they emphasise most apart from the lessons themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 
I can't tell you, I know we - we - oh we had ballroom dancing. Yes. Mr and Mrs Shoulders. And we had ballroom dancing, that was a jolly good - session. That was after school th
ough. From half past four 'til five or something like - for half an hour. Yes, run by the school. But - we had this ballroom dancing, and I loved it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Were they strict about tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 I don't know, we were always tidy - we were always tidy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Oh yes. Yes, I was never late. No, I liked school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Some teachers seem to make much more to-do about that kind of thing than others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Yes. Yes, some do. Well of course it's up to the children, but I thought we - I think with us 
we thought we was in a - w - it was a grammar school - different - you know what I mean? It's - in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13985300\charrsid3306671 modern,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 
 now - nowadays it's the grammar school and they are a different - type, of course they're older. But in our school we just thought we were a bit better than the others. I always used to think so anyway. - Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Were there any groups in the school who felt a bit left out of things though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 No. No. Not in our school. I think it was mea that was left out of things more because they were - a coup
le of them in my class were - teachers children. And they went off - they went away - sat for something and they went away. I had to sit for an exam to be able to leave at thirteen. Yes. Yes. And I left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 What about punishment in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Well
 I - evidently I - I was a good girl, I never had any. Well I liked school, that was the - the answer. I don't think there was anything - ever - with us. No, I don't remember anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Your parents were interested, you said your mother was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 My mother. My mother was. But - dad, no, he was always out at work. And came home and had his meal and sat for a while, went to bed.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Did she came up to the school to see what was going on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 No. No. - No. But - she only ever came when I was young - ve
ry young. I was about six probably, and I was sewing then. And - she came up. I remember that only, when I was very young. But - never again. I don't - and I couldn't think whether she went to the others. I don't remember her }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13985300\charrsid3306671 ever}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671  going, not Southwark Park
 school. Which was nearly opposite, that was all right. She might have slipped over and I - I wouldn't know while I was at my school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 But she asked you what you were doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Yes. Yes. She was very - she was interested, and she - you know, she wou
ld like us all to have done better. I can only say that. I know she - she thought a lot of us with our school - schooling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 You say you left at thirteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Do you wish you'd stayed on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Oh - yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Why did you leave?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 We
ll I had to go out and earn some money. It wasn't my wish but I just had to sit for the exam - because she wanted me to go out to work. I think my - my brother was fourteen. I think they were all fourteen. Glad left - just before her birthday, she was fou
rteen in the August, well - school broke up in July so she left. And she got a job straight away. And she was there a week and they sacked her, because she wasn't - she was under age. Although - the man came up and said she was under age. That was at - }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9190934\charrsid3306671 Atkinson\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 
 I think, the scent - she was in the office there, anyway she was sacked so she immediately went to Peak Freans. And of course was in the office there. Biscuit place, yes. 'Cos we lived under the shadow of them - really. A shadow of Peak Freans build
ing. I think they nearly all went to - Peak Freans.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Nearly all your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Yes. The girls did. And - I think one boy did. Until you get fed up and change.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Did you have to - how did you get into this higher grade school, did you have to pay a fee or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 
No. No, I didn't. I couldn't tell you how I got in but I was there because we lived nearly opposite. One entrance. We lived there in the buildings when I was little. And - I can't tell you how - it wasn't far away, Russell Scott
 buildings, so she must have taken me in and they - I was - I was under - under the age - I don't know - I should have been five I suppose, but they were all three grade - there was the primary, you know, the small school. It was a very good school. For t
h
ose days I mean. 'Cos don't forget - 1900 something, Queen Victoria's time, it was - it was something to have a good school with a - with a - cookery place, you know, I mean for to do all your cookery. That's another out - brick out building. It was very 
- I liked my school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 When you were at school you didn't have a part time job did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 At school - no. No. Just helping mum at home. It wasn't - yes, yes, that's quite enough, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 What was the first job you had when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Wh
en I first went out, I - I went out to - packing chocolates. Nestles. The special offer, Nestle. And I went there and I got four shillings a week. It's a fair walk. Down dockside somewhere. And I got my four shillings a week and brought it home - see that
 
is different in those days, we brought our money home and gave it to them - gave the parents or to mum. Dad wasn't there. But - my brothers and all, just the same, Glad - she was telling me on the phone. We - we just gave her our money, at first, until we
 
got more. 'Til we got up to fifteen shillings a week, and then of course, we just gave mum a certain amount, I don't know what it was now. I can't tell you. Glad gave up fifteen shillings when she started so she said. No, no, she earnt fifteen shillings. 
Ninepence a week rise, after the first six months. Second six months she had a shilling a week rise, this is Peak Freans, 'cos she was sacked from her first job. But - you see, money's so different.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Did you think it was a fair wage at the time then, four shillings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 
Well I suppose we did. Well if mum could work all day for two - oh, two and nine, slogging. No, not all day. It would be more than one day, probably two days, two and nine, that four shillings I brought home was - you know, very good help for her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 So you felt you were doing well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Oh yes. But it was just done, we took it for granted that - that what was life all - life was all about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 How did you get the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Oh I just went, I don't know. I don't think mum went - we went - mum and I went with all the others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Can you remember the first days of going up there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 No, I don't remember. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Do you remember exactly what you did in the factory?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Well N was packing these - in boxes about - like that. There 
was bars of Nestles - yes, bars of Nestles and you'd got to pack - put some of everything in, one of everything. I think they were presentation boxes. Think. I wasn't there too long, 'cos I - what did I do to get more money, I think I went to - to George 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9190934\charrsid3306671 Payne\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 , that was on the Tower Bridge corner, packing tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 While you were packing chocolates were there a lot of girls there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Oh yes. All us - all girls - all young girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 How did you get on with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Oh all right. Except that I was s
o horrified at the language of some of them, 'cos we never heard anything wrong indoors. And it was worse when I went to George Payne, packing tea. It was - there were great big machines and - thing used to come round with all the - packets and tea was au
t
omatic you know, and you took them off and folded them and stuck - yes, but that - I didn't like that because - because of the - the - the girls, the women there. There was women and girls. I didn't like their language. Nor what they was talking about. No
t that I knew anything about it. If you knew what Glad and I'd been talking about on the phone - we were as innocent as anything, 'til we married. Doesn't seem possible does it? But it - that's -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 They were talking about that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Yes. 
Yes. And - awful language. So I didn't stay there long. In the end I went over the Bridge - to - to machining. Ah. Then I was in me element.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Do you remember your wage when you were tea packing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Tea packing I think I got nine shillings a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Did you meet the employer at either of those first two jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 
No. No. No. No. There was a - yes, in the tea packing there was a man walking round, to see to the machinery really. Because there was all these great big things coming down. But - no, w
e never went - met any bosses. Not like I did when I went machining. That was different. Different life altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Could you tell me about that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Well, no, except that I - I just - went to the firm, they were - they used to put notices out,
 machinists wanted, well that suited me for a while 'til I got more experience.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 What was the name of the firm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 I - Lewis Williams. Lewis Williams. And it was Mrs - they were evidently two people that ran the firm. But Mrs Lewis used to come roun
d and - was all power machines like that, and you had to have - a piece of material - I mean, you'd never-finish - like that. You had to have a little square of material, finish with that, because you were wasting cotton. True. And if Mrs Lewis didn't see
 
this - runner, she called it, if she didn't see a runner on the side of your machine with all the lines on, where you'd finished up, you were told off. Gets you very - mean. I still do it now sometimes. Yes. Yes, she used to walk round these rows of girls
, you know. Say, beware, Mrs Lewis is coming. And she would be looking to see if you'd got your runner there. I - I don't know what I got there, didn't get much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 How many girls were there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Oh a lot. About fifty. There were rows of - might ha
ve been sixty. Three long benches with all machines on - one each side. Must have been sixty, could have been more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 What was the talk there like then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Oh, nothing - not - nothing exceptional. We were all there, we'd got to - got to work because of Mrs Lewis coming by.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Were you not allowed to talk when you were working there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 You couldn't talk much because of the power going, you can't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Because of the noise?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Yes. No, you just go on with your work. And I soon left there. And
 I went to - the West End then. I got a job - a city - a - a court dressmaker. Oh I went to the West End as a court dressmaker. And in court dressmaker you all sit round a table doing your various bits by hand. And I did. At - Revel and }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9190934\charrsid3306671 Rossiters}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671  it was, t
he name of the firm, not there now. Near Wroths. But - that's where I really learnt me trade. Real - to - for dressmaking. Until then well I was only just a machinist doing anything that came along. Then after sometime at that I left then and - went as a 
sample hand, in the West End, the Tottenham Court Road. And - I got paid about thirty shillings a week there, just doing the samples. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 What did you do as a sample hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Well, make the dresses. The - the one who designs them - you make it to 
her design, you know, she tells you what to do. You're - you don't have to work for your living. That's all I can say. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 You mean that you're not paid by piecework?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 No. You just make - I got - about thirty shillings a week by that time. and - and of course you - and - you just do what they tell you.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 That's not in a large group then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 No. No, I was on me own. I think there was another sample hand there, but I worked with one cutter - oh - whoever she was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 In your previous job as a dressmaker how did you get on with the other girls there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 All right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 You didn't sort of strike up any friendships?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 No. No. No, never had any friendships with me work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 None at all through your work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Not through my work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Why do you think that was?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Probably our upbringing. To be sort of loners. We were so self sufficient indoors but we didn't make friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Would you join in say at meal breaks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Oh yes, we'd all sit round together. Yes. We used to take our own
 food. Yes. There was an oven there and you could heat up anything. But - you - we'd sit round talking but - not as a friend. What I call friends. No. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9190934\charrsid3306671 
And it probably is our upbringing - upbringing as Glas was saying on the phone this week. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 We were a moody - not }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9190934\charrsid3306671 moody}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671  lot but we - we just - we never dis - never discussed anything that went on indoors - outside. And mother and her loaf. Poor Mr Jones. She wouldn't take it in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 So you never had much fun in the work place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 You don't remember any kind of good laughs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 
Oh no. No. Well it was all work in those days, you had to earn your money in those days. You had to, you were working from half past eight in the morning until six at night. That was our times then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 That's at most of those jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Most of the jobs, that was your - your time. And you'd got to get there, often I would walk it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 The whole way to the West End?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Yes. To save a ha'penny on the bus - on the - the horse bus. Coming home in the wet. It was. No, I
 think I enjoyed the journey more than anything else. I looked forward - to being out. But it's just my make up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Did you work with a particular designer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Yes. When I was at - in Tottenham Court Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 A man or a woman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 A woman. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 You got to know her then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Well - to a point. No. I don't think I did. I don't think I was that kind of - I wasn't sociable enough I don't think.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 What sort of person was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 I don't know, I can't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 You don't remember really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 No, I've forgotten now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 How long were you there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 'Til just before I married. I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 So you were there quite a long time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7043539 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 Some time, yes. And then just before I married I started at a firm doing neckwear. Machining. Right,
 well I liked that, Mrs Robey. And - then I married, then I went back and brought the work home, that's the machine. Or - I bought it. A - a few years ago, I bought since I've been here. And - she died the same year as my - no - yes, she died the same yea
r
 as my husband, but - I did - no, I was - I must have bought that there - bought that at Hornchurch then. Don't remember it coming. Well anyway, she died and - I worked for her all my married life. Oh - you know, periods on and off. But - she was - she wa
s friendly. Very nice woman. That was in the West End. Mrs. Robey.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14100231 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11500731\charrsid3306671 You've not had any other jobs apart from the dressmaking?
