t
 stay in that place on me own. Yes, I like it. I change from room to room. Or I did do in the past, I don't now. When I first - my daughter-in-law used to ring up and say, what room are you in to night. She lived at Arlesford then. What room - number seve
n
 or number five That's when I first - soon after I moved in. Yes. No, I think, it's - it's just that probably I like being alone. That's why I talk so much probably. Yes. Still - I think we're all alike. We're all alike, us lot. Yes, all us Gardners are. 
